irtual environment folders, SQLite database files, and Python cache directories. I'm also adding `.env.example` file with basic setup for local development. I am now working on adding a basic `.env.example` in the backend folder.\n\n\n**Documenting Core Processes**\n\nI'm now documenting core processes. I am writing `backend/requirements.txt` with FastAPI, Uvicorn, SQLAlchemy, Pydantic, pydantic-settings, and python-dotenv. I am working on a `backend/README.md` to ensure clear setup and run instructions, emphasizing its role as a foundation for local development.\n\n\n**Documenting Infrastructure Details**\n\nI'm now documenting the key infrastructure components. I am summarizing the backend architecture. I'm focusing on providing details of all of the folders and files. I am working on the essential documentation required.\n\n\n**Finalizing Frontend Integration**\n\nI'm now integrating the `/api/v1/health` endpoint with dynamic database verification and platform health checks. I'm aligning CORS and request timing telemetry with the frontend requirements to streamline the Next.js integration. I'm configuring an automatic redirect for the root `/` path to the interactive OpenAPI UI (`/docs`).\n\n\n**Launching the Server**\n\nI've successfully launched the Uvicorn development server on port 8000 using `uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000`. I can now access the interactive OpenAPI documentation at [http://localhost:8000/docs](http://localhost:8000/docs), and the health check endpoint at [http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health](http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health) is live.\n\n\n"}}
